title: For Sale:  FS:  Walther PPQ M1 9mm
postcontent: FS is a used, great condition Walther PPQ M1 9 mm.Only 200 rounds shot....great condition.The Walther PPQ M1 is Walther's premier line of state of the art handguns for the Walther family of firearms. The Walther PPQ M1 is great for self defense and target training at the range. The M1 features a European style ambidextrous magazine paddle release. The PPQ M1 is the result of an updated and improved Walther P99 which predated the PPQ by 15 years. The PPQ M1 debuted back in 2011 and was an enhanced version of the P99 RAD for the Polish Military. The main difference from the P99 is the absence of the chamber indicator located on the back of the slide. The PPQ does away with this feature and just adds a back plate similar to other striker fired handguns. The Walther PPQ features ambidextrous slide release levers that are low profile and easy to manipulate in either hand. The most notable difference is the trigger system. The P99 has two different trigger modes depending on which version you purchase.  The PPQ features the QDT trigger or (Quick Defense Trigger) which basically means that the trigger system includes a safety tang in the middle of the trigger so that if you don't position your finger properly on the trigger the gun will not fire, nor will it fire if it is dropped. The Walther PPQ M1 comes with two 15 round magazines, a magazine loader, and interchangeable back straps.  If you are in the market for a high quality, fully featured handgun with fantastic ergonomics and an exceptional trigger, then look no further than the Walther PPQ M1 9mm.

postcontent: ASK ABOUT OUR 60-DAY LAY-A-WAY!!!For sale is a NEW Daniel Defense ISR 300BLK.  This rifle only requires one tax stamp.  This rifle does require a $200 tax stamp and an NFA Form 4 Application, which is easier than it sounds, and we will be happy to walk you through the entire process.     The Daniel Defense DDM4ISR is our Integrally Suppressed Weapon System optimized for the .300 Blackout cartridge. Built around a 9”, Cold Hammer Forged barrel that is fluted along with a target crown and a standard pistol-length gas system, this versatile, high-performance rifle is the complete package, accurately delivering both subsonic and supersonic projectiles downrange with unrelenting reliability. Because the suppressor is an integral part of the barrel, this weapon system is ready for service right out of the box. There’s no attaching a suppressor and wondering if it’s mounted correctly and/or properly aligned. There’s no re-zeroing for suppressed vs. unsuppressed fire.  The DDM4ISR’s integral suppressor extends the barrel to an NFA-required 16 inches in length, so this platform is not classified as a Short Barreled Rifle (SBR) and therefore only requires a single tax stamp (for the suppressor). The suppressor’s lightweight outer tube is constructed of durable, heat-resistant metal alloys and coated with a protective high-temperature Cerakote-C finish, which is able of withstanding extreme temperatures and harsh environments. The suppressor is also user-serviceable, so its baffle core can be easily removed for periodic cleaning in order to maintain peak performance.   The DDM4ISR comes standard with Daniel Defense’s MFR XL 15.0 modular handguard, which features a continuous 1913 Picatinny rail on its top, for the mounting of iron sights or optics, and Keymod attachment points on the sides and bottom. This longer, multi-functional handguard, in conjunction with a Daniel Defense Buttstock and Pistol Grip, make the DDM4ISR as ergonomic and maneuverable as it is versatile.
